#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn9.14"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.14:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.14:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga "
msgstr "1. In the Woods "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 14. Gandhatthenasutta → padumapupphasuttaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts2) | padumapuppha (puṇḍarika) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.14:0.3"
msgid "14. Gandhatthenasutta "
msgstr "14. The Thief of Scent "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.440, sc1
msgctxt "sn9.14:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu viharati aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe. "
msgstr "At one time one of the mendicants was staying in the land of the Kosalans in a certain forest grove. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.14:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu pacchābhattaṃ piṇḍapātapaṭikkanto pokkharaṇiṃ ogāhetvā padumaṃ upasiṅghati. "
msgstr "Now at that time, after the meal, on their return from alms-round, that mendicant plunged into a lotus pond and sniffed a pink lotus. "

msgctxt "sn9.14:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno anukampikā atthakāmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ saṃvejetukāmā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "The deity haunting that forest had compassion for that mendicant, and wanted what’s best for them. So they approached that mendicant wanting to stir them up, and addressed them in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn9.14:2.1"
msgid "“Yametaṃ vārijaṃ pupphaṃ, "
msgstr "“This water flower has not been given. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:2.2"
msgid "adinnaṃ upasiṅghasi; "
msgstr "When you sniff it, "

# NOTE: This is, of course, poetry. In the Vinaya, to be theft it must be something someone owns, and they must perceive it as taken and lost to them.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:2.3"
msgid "Ekaṅgametaṃ theyyānaṃ, "
msgstr "this is one factor of theft. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:2.4"
msgid "gandhatthenosi mārisā”ti. "
msgstr "Good sir, you are a thief of scent!” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn9.14:3.1"
msgid "“Na harāmi na bhañjāmi, "
msgstr "“I do not take, nor do I break; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:3.2"
msgid "ārā siṅghāmi vārijaṃ; "
msgstr "I sniff the water flower from afar. "

# NOTE: https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/can-va-a-mean-reason/3604
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:3.3"
msgid "Atha kena nu vaṇṇena, "
msgstr "So based on what evidence "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:3.4"
msgid "gandhatthenoti vuccati. "
msgstr "do you call me a thief of scent? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.441, sc4
msgctxt "sn9.14:4.1"
msgid "Yvāyaṃ bhisāni khanati, "
msgstr "Why don’t you accuse someone "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:4.2"
msgid "puṇḍarīkāni bhañjati; "
msgstr "who does such vandalizing "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ ākiṇṇakammanto, "
msgstr "as digging up the roots, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:4.4"
msgid "kasmā eso na vuccatī”ti. "
msgstr "or breaking off the flowers?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.205, sc5
msgctxt "sn9.14:5.1"
msgid "“Ākiṇṇaluddo puriso, "
msgstr "“I have nothing to say "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:5.2"
msgid "dhāticelaṃva makkhito; "
msgstr "to a person who is a crude vandal, "

# NOTE: Wow, what an exact simile!
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:5.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ me vacanaṃ natthi, "
msgstr "soiled like a used nappy. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:5.4"
msgid "tvañcārahāmi vattave. "
msgstr "You’re the one who deserves to be spoken to. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn9.14:6.1"
msgid "Anaṅgaṇassa posassa, "
msgstr "To the man who has not a blemish "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:6.2"
msgid "niccaṃ sucigavesino; "
msgstr "who is always seeking purity, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:6.3"
msgid "Vālaggamattaṃ pāpassa, "
msgstr "even a hair-tip of evil "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:6.4"
msgid "abbhāmattaṃva khāyatī”ti. "
msgstr "seems as big as a cloud.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn9.14:7.1"
msgid "“Addhā maṃ yakkha jānāsi, "
msgstr "“Indeed, O spirit, you understand me, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:7.2"
msgid "atho me anukampasi; "
msgstr "and you empathize with me. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:7.3"
msgid "Punapi yakkha vajjāsi, "
msgstr "Please speak to me again, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:7.4"
msgid "yadā passasi edisan”ti. "
msgstr "whenever you see something like this.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.442, sc8
msgctxt "sn9.14:8.1"
msgid "“Neva taṃ upajīvāma, "
msgstr "“I’m no dependent of yours, "

# NOTE: Sick burn, deva.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:8.2"
msgid "napi te bhatakāmhase; "
msgstr "nor am I your servant. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:8.3"
msgid "Tvameva bhikkhu jāneyya, "
msgstr "You yourself should know, mendicant, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:8.4"
msgid "yena gaccheyya suggatin”ti. "
msgstr "the way that leads to a good place.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn9.14:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti. "
msgstr "Impelled by that deity, that mendicant was struck with a sense of urgency. "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn9.14:9.2"
msgid "Vanavaggo paṭhamo. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn9.14:10.1"
msgid "Vivekaṃ upaṭṭhānañca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:10.2"
msgid "Kassapagottena sambahulā; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:10.3"
msgid "Ānando anuruddho ca, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:10.4"
msgid "Nāgadattañca kulagharaṇī. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "sn9.14:11.1"
msgid "Vajjiputto ca vesālī, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:11.2"
msgid "Sajjhāyena ayoniso; "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:11.3"
msgid "Majjhanhikālamhi pākatindriya—"
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn9.14:11.4"
msgid "Padumapupphena cuddasa bhaveti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn9.14:11.5"
msgid "Vanasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ. "
msgstr "The Linked Discourses in the Forest are completed."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
